Installing without root access on Linux:

## Installing python
cd ~
mkdir python3
cd python3
wget https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.5.2/Python-3.5.2.tar.xz
tar xvf Python-3.5.2.tar.xz
cd Python-3.5.2
./configure prefix=/home/<user_name>/python3
make install

## Installing required modules
cd ../bin
./pip3 install numpy scipy pandas matplotlib python-igraph biopython glob2
cd ~

## Downloading syri
git clone https://www.github.com/schneebergerlab/syri

## Installing syri
cd syri
../python3/bin/python3 setup.py install


syri is installed.. Can be used in as python module using import syri, or as commandline tool by adding /home/<user_name>/python3/bin in PATH. Three tools are installed there SynSearch, scaffoldOrder, and getSVs.
